  "text": "Chromium's multi-process architecture is built on five key components:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** (content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h/.cc)\n   - Browser-side representation of a renderer process\n   - Manages the lifecycle and communication with a specific renderer process\n   - Implements the ChildProcessLauncher::Client and mojom::RendererHost interfaces\n   - Hosts the IPC channel between browser and renderer processes\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** (content/browser/browser_main_loop.h/.cc)\n   - The main event loop of the browser process\n   - Orchestrates browser initialization and shutdown sequences\n   - Manages critical browser threads and services\n   - Called from BrowserMainRunner to execute main browser process stages\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** (content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h/.cc)\n   - Main thread of a renderer process where blink::WebView instances live\n   - Implements the mojom::Renderer interface for receiving browser-to-renderer messages\n   - Handles routing of legacy IPC messages based on routing IDs corresponding to RenderFrameImpl instances\n   - Manages renderer process initialization and resource allocation\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** (content/browser/child_process_launcher.h/.cc)\n   - Responsible for asynchronously spawning child processes\n   - Notifies clients when process launch succeeds or fails\n   - Avoids blocking the calling thread during process creation (often takes >100ms)\n   - Provides the Client interface that processes must implement\n\n5. **content.mojom.Renderer** (content/common/renderer.mojom)\n   - Mojo interface definition for browser-to-renderer communication\n   - Implements the primordial channel-associated interface in the render process\n   - Used for control messages that need to retain FIFO ordering with legacy IPC messages\n   - Methods include CreateAgentSchedulingGroup and various configuration commands\n\nThese components work together to implement Chromium's multi-process model where the browser process manages renderer processes, communicates with them through Mojo IPC and legacy IPC channels, and coordinates their execution and resource usage."
}

